   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8cf5a7e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# VGGT-Omega JAX Inference Demo (Memory-Optimized)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to perform inference on **VGGT-Omega 1B 512** using JAX under strict memory constraints:\n",
    "1. **Under 10 GB RAM** using JIT compilation, bfloat16 precision, and template-free direct Msgpack restoring.\n",
    "2. **Under 4 GB RAM** using eager (no-JIT) execution, float16 precision, and memory-mapped parameter files on disk."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc1ca183",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Import Dependencies and Setup Backend"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "fc95406d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import glob\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import resource\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "\n",
    "# Force CPU backend if GPU libraries/drivers are mismatched. \n",
    "# Remove or set to \"gpu\" if JAX CUDA is configured.\n",
    "os.environ[\"JAX_PLATFORMS\"] = \"cpu\"\n",
    "\n",
    "import jax\n",
    "import jax.numpy as jnp\n",
    "\n",
    "from vggt_omega.jax.models import VGGTOmega as JAXModel\n",
    "from vggt_omega.jax.load_weights import load_checkpoint\n",
    "from vggt_omega.utils.load_fn import load_and_preprocess_images\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"JAX Backend: {jax.default_backend().upper()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Devices: {jax.devices()}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "def get_peak_ram_mb():\n",
    "    return resource.getrusage(resource.RUSAGE_SELF).ru_maxrss / 1024.0\n",
    "print(f\"Initial RAM usage: {get_peak_ram_mb():.2f} MB\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2d4fa4da",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1.5 Download Dataset and Converted Weights\n",
    "We download the NERF 360 pinecone dataset and converted weights. Note that low-RAM options require different weights formats:\n",
    "- **bfloat16 file** (`vggt_omega_1b_512_bf16.msgpack.zst`): Fits in <10 GB RAM.\n",
    "- **float16 memory-mapped folder** (`vggt_omega_1b_512_fp16_mmap`): Fits in <4 GB RAM."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b7e4614d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import urllib.request\n",
    "import zipfile\n",
    "\n",
    "def download_file(url, filepath):\n",
    "    if os.path.exists(filepath):\n",
    "        print(f\"File {filepath} already exists. Skipping download.\")\n",
    "        return\n",
    "    print(f\"Downloading {url} to {filepath}...\")\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        req = urllib.request.Request(\n",
    "            url, \n",
    "            headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64)'}\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        with urllib.request.urlopen(req) as response, open(filepath, 'wb') as out_file:\n",
    "            chunk_size = 16 * 1024 * 1024  # 16 MB chunks\n",
    "            while True:\n",
    "                chunk = response.read(chunk_size)\n",
    "                if not chunk:\n",
    "                    break\n",
    "                out_file.write(chunk)\n",
    "        print(f\"Successfully downloaded {filepath}.\")\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        if os.path.exists(filepath):\n",
    "            os.remove(filepath)\n",
    "        print(f\"Error downloading {filepath}: {e}\")\n",
    "        raise e\n",
    "\n",
    "# Download dataset if not present\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(\"pinecone\"):\n",
    "    zip_path = \"nerf_real_360.zip\"\n",
    "    download_file(\n",
    "        \"https://huggingface.co/datasets/1kaiser/NERF_360/resolve/main/nerf_real_360.zip?download=true\", \n",
    "        zip_path\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(\"Extracting nerf_real_360.zip...\")\n",
    "    with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_path, 'r') as zip_ref:\n",
    "        zip_ref.extractall(\".\")\n",
    "    print(\"Extraction complete.\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Dataset directory pinecone/ already exists.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Download JAX bfloat16 weights if not present\n",
    "download_file(\n",
    "    \"https://huggingface.co/datasets/1kaiser/vggt-omega-jax/resolve/main/vggt_omega_1b_512_bf16.msgpack.zst\", \n",
    "    \"vggt_omega_1b_512_bf16.msgpack.zst\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(\"Ensure 'vggt_omega_1b_512_fp16_mmap' exists for the ultra-low-RAM mode.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc9e3e7a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Option Selection: Select Your Memory Budget"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d7f1dc20",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Choose configuration:\n",
    "# 'low_ram'  : bfloat16, JIT compiled, direct checkpoint restoration. Budget: <10 GB RAM.\n",
    "# 'mmap_eager': float16, eager execution, memory-mapped parameters. Budget: <4 GB RAM.\n",
    "MEMORY_MODE = 'low_ram'\n",
    "\n",
    "if MEMORY_MODE == 'low_ram':\n",
    "    print(\"Configuring JAX model in bfloat16 (JIT enabled)...\")\n",
    "    jax_model = JAXModel(\n",
    "        patch_size=16,\n",
    "        embed_dim=1024,\n",
    "        enable_camera=True,\n",
    "        enable_depth=True,\n",
    "        enable_alignment=False,\n",
    "        dtype=jnp.bfloat16\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Direct load of parameters bypassing template init saves 7.2 GB of RAM\n",
    "    checkpoint_path = \"vggt_omega_1b_512_bf16.msgpack.zst\"\n",
    "    print(f\"Restoring weights template-free from: {checkpoint_path}...\")\n",
    "    restored_params = load_checkpoint(None, checkpoint_path)\n",
    "    print(f\"Loaded. Peak RAM usage: {get_peak_ram_mb():.2f} MB\")\n",
    "\n",
    "elif MEMORY_MODE == 'mmap_eager':\n",
    "    print(\"Configuring JAX model in float16 (Eager/mmap)...\")\n",
    "    # Increase file descriptor limit for memory-mapping\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        soft, hard = resource.getrlimit(resource.RLIMIT_NOFILE)\n",
    "        resource.setrlimit(resource.RLIMIT_NOFILE, (32768, hard))\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Warning: could not increase open file limit: {e}\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "    jax_model = JAXModel(\n",
    "        patch_size=16,\n",
    "        embed_dim=1024,\n",
    "        enable_camera=True,\n",
    "        enable_depth=True,\n",
    "        enable_alignment=False,\n",
    "        dtype=jnp.float16\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Recursively load parameter directory into memory-mapped NumPy views\n",
    "    def load_recursive(current_dir):\n",
    "        d = {}\n",
    "        for entry in os.scandir(current_dir):\n",
    "            if entry.is_dir():\n",
    "                d[entry.name] = load_recursive(entry.path)\n",
    "            elif entry.is_file() and entry.name.endswith(\".npy\"):\n",
    "                key = entry.name[:-4]\n",
    "                d[key] = np.load(entry.path, mmap_mode='r')\n",
    "        return d\n",
    "        \n",
    "    mmap_path = \"vggt_omega_1b_512_fp16_mmap\"\n",
    "    print(f\"Memory mapping weights from directory: {mmap_path}...\")\n",
    "    restored_params = load_recursive(mmap_path)\n",
    "    print(f\"Loaded (mapped parameters occupy 0 MB RAM). Peak RAM usage: {get_peak_ram_mb():.2f} MB\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6ce9caa2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Preprocess Input Images\n",
    "We load real images from the `pinecone/images/` directory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "be34b674",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "image_dir = \"pinecone/images\"\n",
    "image_paths = sorted(glob.glob(os.path.join(image_dir, \"*\")))[:2]\n",
    "print(f\"Selected Images:\")\n",
    "for p in image_paths:\n",
    "    print(f\"  - {os.path.basename(p)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Preprocess to shape [1, T, C, H, W]\n",
    "x_pt = load_and_preprocess_images(image_paths, image_resolution=512, patch_size=16)\n",
    "x_pt = x_pt.unsqueeze(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Transpose to channels_last for JAX -> [1, T, H, W, C]\n",
    "x_jax = jnp.array(x_pt.permute(0, 1, 3, 4, 2).numpy())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cast input to match the chosen model precision\n",
    "if MEMORY_MODE == 'low_ram':\n",
    "    x_input = x_jax.astype(jnp.bfloat16)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    x_input = x_jax.astype(jnp.float16)\n",
    "print(f\"Input shape: {x_input.shape}, dtype: {x_input.dtype}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c07777f3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Run Model Inference\n",
    "Depending on the mode, we run using either **JIT compilation** or **eager layer-by-layer** execution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7f9075cb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if MEMORY_MODE == 'low_ram':\n",
    "    # Low RAM compiles and executes on CPU/GPU\n",
    "    @jax.jit\n",
    "    def jax_predict(params, x):\n",
    "        return jax_model.apply(params, x)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    print(\"Running cold run (compiling kernel + execution)...\")\n",
    "    t0 = time.time()\n",
    "    preds = jax_predict(restored_params, x_input)\n",
    "    for k, v in preds.items():\n",
    "        if isinstance(v, jnp.ndarray):\n",
    "            v.block_until_ready()\n",
    "    print(f\"Cold run completed in {time.time() - t0:.2f} seconds\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Running warm run...\")\n",
    "    t0 = time.time()\n",
    "    preds = jax_predict(restored_params, x_input)\n",
    "    for k, v in preds.items():\n",
    "        if isinstance(v, jnp.ndarray):\n",
    "            v.block_until_ready()\n",
    "    print(f\"Warm run completed in {time.time() - t0:.4f} seconds\")\n",
    "\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    # Ultra-low RAM runs in eager mode layer-by-layer.\n",
    "    # JAX reads weight files on-the-fly and discards them, keeping parameter footprint at 0 MB\n",
    "    print(\"Running eager layer-by-layer inference (no JIT compilation)... \")\n",
    "    t0 = time.time()\n",
    "    preds = jax_model.apply(restored_params, x_input)\n",
    "    for k, v in preds.items():\n",
    "        if isinstance(v, jnp.ndarray):\n",
    "            v.block_until_ready()\n",
    "    print(f\"Eager inference completed in {time.time() - t0:.2f} seconds\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Peak RAM after inference: {get_peak_ram_mb():.2f} MB\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8f7ea829",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Visualize Predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8c68e3db",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "depth_maps = np.array(preds[\"depth\"])\n",
    "depth_conf = np.array(preds[\"depth_conf\"])\n",
    "print(f\"Depth shape: {depth_maps.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Pose vector shape (B, T, 9): {preds['pose_enc'].shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(14, 8))\n",
    "for i in range(2):\n",
    "    # 1. Original Image\n",
    "    img_np = (x_jax[0, i] * np.array([0.229, 0.224, 0.225]) + np.array([0.485, 0.456, 0.406])).clip(0, 1)\n",
    "    axes[i, 0].imshow(img_np)\n",
    "    axes[i, 0].set_title(f\"Frame {i} Image\")\n",
    "    axes[i, 0].axis(\"off\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # 2. Predicted Depth Map\n",
    "    im1 = axes[i, 1].imshow(depth_maps[0, i, ..., 0], cmap=\"inferno\")\n",
    "    axes[i, 1].set_title(f\"Frame {i} Predicted Depth\")\n",
    "    axes[i, 1].axis(\"off\")\n",
    "    fig.colorbar(im1, ax=axes[i, 1], fraction=0.046, pad=0.04)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # 3. Predicted Depth Confidence\n",
    "    im2 = axes[i, 2].imshow(depth_conf[0, i], cmap=\"viridis\")\n",
    "    axes[i, 2].set_title(f"Frame {i} Depth Confidence\")\n",
    "    axes[i, 2].axis(\"off\")\n",
    "    fig.colorbar(im2, ax=axes[i, 2], fraction=0.046, pad=0.04)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
